<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Trojan" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Trojan</orth> (O. Edd. <emph>Troian</emph> or <emph>Troyan</emph>) 1) subst. a native of Troy: <bibl n="shak. luc 1551" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1551</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.5.106" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 5, 106</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 1, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.233" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 233</bibl> etc.<lb />Used as a cant term for persons of a doubtful character: <cit><quote>Hector was but a T. in respect of this,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.640" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 640</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>unless you play the honest T., the poor wench is cast away,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.640" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 640</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>there are other --s than thou dreamest not of,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 1, 77</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>base T.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 5.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 1, 20</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 1, 20</bibl>
<lb />2) adj. pertaining to Troy: <bibl n="shak. luc 1431" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1431</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 5.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.181" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 181</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.181" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 181</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 13</bibl> etc. <bibl n="shak. per 1.4.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 4, 93</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>